data.title: King's Granddaughter Is Married in Sweden
data.text:
STOCKHOLM, June 5—Princess Désirée, a granddaughter of King Gustaf VI Adolf of Sweden, was married to Baron Niclas Silfverschiold today in the Lutheran Cathedral here.

The 26-year‐old Princess and the 30-year‐old Swedish nobleman took their vows before 800 people headed by the royal family and foreign royalty. The simple Swedish Lutheran ceremony was performed by Archbishop Gunnar Hultgren of Uppsala, primate of the state church. It was carried to the nation on television.

The Princess, whose father is dead, was escorted by her grand daughter.
